POEMS

Through thee, the Truth in glory chinea

On broken altars, falh’ng shrines:

Thus Faith the crown of triumph wore, A bloodless conqueror.

Hell launches myriad angry darts And proves a hundred subtle arte The fruita of victory to steal

And quench thy til-eleas zeal.

Let Flavius work his tyrant will—

'I'hou only standeet firmet still:

Nor taunts, nor threaoe, nor chaine oan' bind Thy free and fearless mind.

Yon, rather, to his lumel-maath The Hero hantone, while his brath, Foeble with age and battling long,

The loving Lord makes strong. 99
